news.title: China's Shimao Group seeks buyer for Hong Kong hotel: JLL
news.para: Shanghai-based Shimao, in the process of restructuring $11.8 billion of offshore debt, is among the many Chinese developers that defaulted last year.

news.title: DHFL case: SC dismisses ED appeal, says grant of default bail duration to include remand period
news.para: "The remand period will be calculated from the date, magistrate remand the accused. An accused becomes entitled to default bail if the charge sheet is not filed by 61st or 91st day of the remand period", the bench said.

news.title: J-K admin will soon make provision to provide land, home to poor: LG
news.para: "The administration is committed to resolve this issue and very soon it will come out with a provision to provide land to the landless families so that they can have their own house," Sinha said at an event here organised to celebrate 450th Prakash Utsav of Goswami Guru Nabha Dass Maharaj.

news.title: Assets of Holy Faith Builders to be auctioned
news.para: There will be 13 properties which will be auctioned and valuation for each plot has also been fixed. Plot by plot auction will be held this time.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body will take over smart city projects only after detailed reports
news.para: In a circular by the commissioner, HDMC informed about the constitution of an expert committee comprising four members. It instructed the experts’ team to submit the report, despite reminders that the team was yet to meet.

news.title: Current work trends: What commercial landlords need to know
NIT refusing to give Nagpur civic body land for housing for poor
news.para: NIT has not shown eagerness to hand over the land to NMC even after the special purpose vehicle Nagpur Smart and Sustainable Development Corporation Limited (NSSCDCL) offered to adjust the value of the land - ₹40 crore - against the share to be paid by NIT for the Smart City Project.

news.title: After six-month survey, 12,000 unassessed properties identified in Secunderabad cantonment board
news.para: With the latest enumeration, the number of properties has shot up from 34,000 to 46,000 properties. Secunderabad Cantonment Board (SCB) officials can expect a substantial increase in property tax collection.

news.title: Bhopal civic body on overdrive for property tax collection as fiscal year nears end
news.para: Since November, Bhopal Municipal Corporation (BMC) has listed names of individual in public domain threating to auction their properties in lieu of tax collection.

news.title: Diesel generators sets in colony green belt in Gurugram: NGT pulls up senior officials for 'inaction'
news.para: The tribunal was hearing a petition filed last year by Gurgaon resident Raman Sharma, who had alleged that 10 diesel generators were being run from a green belt in Malibu Town, Sector 47, and that construction and demolition waste was regularly dumped in the residential colony.

news.title: Borrowers refinance home loans as tenures go beyond retirement
news.para: While floating rates mean that borrowers have to pay the rates prevailing in the market, this may be the best time to refinance loans as lenders are willing to sacrifice some of their margins for new customers.

news.title: On 16th week of protest, Greater Noida West buyers plan to send postcards to PM
news.para: More than 60,000 homebuyers in over 20 societies are awaiting possession and registries of their flats, some for over a decade.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to upload status of 197 projects on website
news.para: The Noida Authority has recently uploaded the details of its 115 projects, including their status of completion and occupation certificates, arrears, disputes and registry of flats, on its website.

news.title: YEIDA plans scheme to collect Rs 4,450 crore from 14 builders
news.para: Officials said that of the Rs 4,457 crore that YEIDA was to collect from the builders, Rs 2,753 crore was land premium, Rs 1,408 crore additional compensation for farmers and Rs 296 crore lease rent.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates new metro line in Bengaluru
news.para: ​Officials said this section is the eastern extension to the operational East-West Corridor (Purple Line) from Baiyappanahalli to Whitefield Station.
